 had just completed Kipling’s “The Rhyme of the Three Sealers” (“Now this is the Law of the Muscovite that he proves with shot and steel”) when he fell ill and soon expired under his splendid painted bed ceil with its reproductions of Altamira animals, his last words in his last delirium being “Comment dit-on ‘mourir’ en anglais?”—a beautiful and touching end.

